data.title: Education Budget 2026 Live Updates: From AI classrooms to workforce skills, here is what to expect as FM - Times of India
data.snippet: Schools received their highest-ever funding, with increased support for Samagra Shiksha, PM-POSHAN, and PM-SHRI Schools. BharatNet began extending broadband to government secondary schools, while digital textbooks in Indian languages under the Bharatiya Bhasha Pustak Scheme aimed to make learning more inclusive.Higher education continued its expansion. Five IITs set up after 2014 received infrastructure upgrades, 6,500 new seats were added, and IIT Patna was earmarked for major development.The PM Research Fellowship expanded support for 10,000 scholars at IITs and IISc. A ₹500-crore Centre of Excellence in Artificial Intelligence for Education signalled a first step towards AI-enabled teaching.Medical education was also being revitalized with an increase of 10,000 seats this year as part [...] Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi 2’ January 31 written update: Ranvijay gets custody, and Gautam takes his revengeNumerology horoscope today, February 01, 2026: What your name's first letter reveals todayGross GST collections in January rise 6.2% to Rs 1.93 lakh crore, net revenue up 7.6%‘Game of Thrones’ fan theories that kept Westeros debates alive long after the finaleQatar announces fuel prices for February 2026: Petrol and diesel rates dropWhile parents rush to private schools, IAS officer sets a shining example by enrolling his 3-year-old in an Anganwadi schoolRam Charan and Upasana welcome twins: ‘Thankful to all our fans, loved ones and well-wishers’Tahir Tahirfuego's cause of death: How did GodLike Esports personality pass away at the age of 24Robert Downey Jr. net worth: A look at [...] with an increase of 10,000 seats this year as part of a more long term goal of 75,000 seats in five years.The scaffolds are being erected. The question to be asked is whether Budget 2026 will turn radically towards the quality of learning, teacher preparedness, and employability.The NEP 2020 is progressive, although the difficult task will be the future.According to the Economic Survey 2025-26, education was outlined as the core part of the growth process in India, with an increase in enrolment and increased career opportunities. The current Gross Enrolment Ratios are 90.9 on the primary level and 90.3 on upper primary level.Today India has 23 IITs, 21 IIMs, and 20 AIIMS, with international IIT campuses in Zanzibar and Abu Dhabi.
